&quot;Henry&quot;<br><br>
A poem by Robert H. Dirr Jr.<br><br>
John digs ditches for the city and<br>
James delivers the US mail and<br>
Sonny's up on the Wall<br>
With Hank and Leon and Julio.<br>
Platoon hit the big screenb with<br>
Cinemascopic blood and I saw<br>
Henry in the cardboard alley<br>
Behind the Provident Bank.<br><br>
The bottle inside his paper bag <br>
Cracked when he hit the ground<br>
And I pretended I didn't know him<br>
To save the embarrassment<br>
Of an accidental twenty-year-reunion.<br>
He looked up and asked me<br>
For a dollar, and I remembered<br>
A job we shared a long time ago.<br><br>
He was waiting for the VA check to arrive<br>
So he could eat something and<br>
Spend a night or two at the <br>
Holiday Inn and I remembered<br>
Me and Henry loading last remains<br>
Into shiny aluminum caskets.<br>
PLEASE ALLOW 4 TO 6 WEEKS FOR<br>
DELIVERY...SATISFACTION GUARANTEED.<br>

